As with every economy of countries around the world hit by this pandemic, there are significant impact of the
lockdown on almost every part of life. For the case of Nigeria, the effect of COVID-19 on food prices is typically
consider significant both for locally produced products as well as imported ones.

The common food items are Beans, Beef, Bread, Catfish, Egg, Frozen Chicken, Garri, Irish potato, local rice, Maize, Plantain, Imported rice,., Yam tuber. Their prices are viewed before (2019) and during COVID-19 (March 2020 - August 2020).
Stable food prices are less and affordable for Nigerian before the Pandemic but there is hike in the prices of these food items during COVID-19 pandemic which can be attributed to the Lockdown.
